	This is a follow-up to   PR bin/11997.
	The goal of this enhancement is to save significant time and disk
	space processing large print jobs coming via mechanisms like samba.
	These are often configured to copy the (large) print file into a
	spool directory, and they then run 'lpr -r' to actually print the
	job.  This change causes 'lpr -r' to simply move the spool file (if
	possible) instead of copying the entire file (thus giving you two
	copies in your spool directory for a moment) only to remove the
	original.

	The update given in bin/11997 had security issues.  This version
	implements the enhancement without opening any security holes.
	Note this includes a few checks which are redundant under FreeBSD,
	but important if compiling this version of lpr under other OS's.

Fix: Here is the new, improved patch.  This is based on the version
	of lpr.c found in freebsd-current as of Dec 23rd 1999.



